07/03/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Serbian President Boris Tadic said on Tuesday (March 6th) that his country would have a new government within two or three weeks.
He said it work for the country's EU integration, reforms and full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal.
The Democratic Party (DS) leader's comments followed talks with EU leaders in Brussels.
In Belgrade meanwhile, consultations on forming the new coalition cabinet continued on Tuesday with separate meetings between DS and the Liberal Democratic Party (LDP)-led coalition, DS and minorities' parties, and the Democratic Party of Serbia (DSS)-New Serbia (NS) coalition and G17 Plus.
(Blic, Danas - 07/03/07;
Beta, B92, Tanjug, RTS - 06/03/07)
